<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The memcpy call can be executed with ActualCopy==0 (e.g. when StubPtr->Data.Buff.Position == StubPtr->Data.Buff.TotalSize or when MaxSize==0). In that case memcpy(..., 0) is a no-op: it is executed but its removal would not affect program behaviour. This constitutes dead code under MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2. A fix is to guard the memcpy (and the subsequent Position increment) with if (ActualCopy > 0).
</scenario>
